Request Flow:

Step 1
User opens:
www.company.com
Route53 resolves DNS.

Step 2
CloudFront serves cached content.
CSS
JavaScript
Images
Videos

Step 3
ALB distributes traffic.

Request 1 → EC2-A
Request 2 → EC2-B
Request 3 → EC2-C

Step 4
Auto Scaling handles demand.

Normal Traffic
      ↓
2 Servers

High Traffic
      ↓
20 Servers

Step 5
Application accesses database.

Orders
Users
Payments
Products

Stored in RDS.

Step 6
Images and backups stored in S3.

Disaster Recovery Scenario
AZ Failure
AZ-A Down
     ↓
AZ-B Active

Application remains available.

Database Failure:

Primary RDS Down
        ↓
Standby RDS Active

Automatic failover.

